&lt;p&gt;    This PR solves the bug described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-7005&quot; title=&quot;Optimization steps are missing for nested registered tables&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-7005&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-7005&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. This PR adds another stage to the optimization phase that converts table scans to full plans. However, it makes 2 rules non-optional. Do we want to make those two rules also configurable through the Calcite config?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This should definitely be part of Flink 1.3.2.&lt;/p&gt;

